Grants News Join the Community Community Guide Discord Telegram Build on Blockstack Coming Soon It s All About Ownership The Stacks Foundation supports the mission of a user owned internet through governance, research and development, education, and Our mission is to deliver the promise of Web 3, where every internet user can participate in the value they create because they have full ownership of their identity, money, and What we do Governance The Stacks Foundation is the home for governance of Blockstack s technology, serving as neutral ground for various parties to come together and reach consensus on the path Research We support independent researchers, contributors, and collaborators to help build a better user owned internet through research and Education We provide tools to educate new users and developers about Blockstack We support the educational resources and forums to share knowledge, like events and community Grants We create new avenues for innovation through funding research, ecosystem development, and developer Who we are Stacks Foundation Board Zavain Dar Zavain is driven by smart software, leveraging data and machine intelligence to scale, augment, and biology, language, manufacturing and He looks for entrepreneurs that can use software and data to hone a philosophical position on where the world is, and how to direct it for the Zavain has led Lux s firm s theses in Genetics, Synthetic Biology, and the Prior to VC, Zavain was a founder and computer At Discovery Engine (acquired by Twitter), he engineered machine learning and AI systems across a Contact | Helping Hands MB Helping Hands MB Home About Us Our Projects Blog Contact More Contact Us ¬©2020 by Helping Proudly created with   Our Projects | Helping Hands Helping Hands Home About Us Our Projects Contact More Our Projects We aim to create a community of students educated with skills that benefit themselves, others, and their STEAM+ Face Shields Printing Club - Our most ambitious and successful project is our STEAM+ The project was to mentor students at a Title 1 elementary school, Biscayne Beach Elementary, about robotics and Learn More - In response to the Pandemic, Helping Hands decided to do something and Members of Helping Hands volunteered to produce plastic face shields for first responders, food distribution volunteers, and Learn More June - Present To allow further outreach towards high school students, Helping Hands organized and operates the Printing Club at Miami Beach Senior This allows us to start more projects, educate more students, and reach deeper into our Learn More STEAM+ Prosthetic Hands Future Plans - Present A continuation of our STEAM+ project, STEAM+ was redesigned in order to be friendly, which meant virtual The project was to mentor graders at Nautilus Middle school about science, electronics, and design printing. Learn More TBA As of now, this is a confirmed future project Helping Hands is working The project is to mentor high school students in the Printing Club at Miami Beach Senior High about design printing so they can produce prosthetic hands for people in need around the Learn More TBA Who knows what the future may hold :) Learn More ¬©2020 by Helping Proudly created with   About Us | Helping Hands Helping Hands Home About Us Our Projects Contact More About Helping Hands Helping Hands MB is a Florida in Miami Beach, that evolved out of a community service project conceived in April by Jonathan Tamen, then Captain of his school‚Äôs FIRST Robotics team, the As a member of the City of Miami Beach Youth Commission, Jonathan asked the Mayor and City Commissioners to sponsor the robotics team in his STEAM+ project idea to mentor elementary students in coding and robotics classes in a fun way using educational LEGOs and a big sister big The project was a huge success, bringing accolades from the Mayor, school principals, teachers, and parents, and most importantly all students ‚Äì both big and ‚Äã When COVID shuttered schools in February , Jonathan encouraged his brother David to try to use the printers in their bedroom to make urgently needed personal protective equipment for first responders in their After several experiments, David designed, created, and made an inexpensive plastic facial shield, running his printers 7. He also taught other high school students to make them, and collectively the group made more than shields donated to doctors, health care workers, police, and municipal workers in the Miami ‚Äã The brothers were featured on the Miami ABC affiliate TV news, television, and the Miami In May , Jonathan and his brother David received a Call for Kindness award from the Riley‚Äôs Way Foundation, with a $3,000 grant for their proposal to launch a Printing Club and a chapter of the engineering charity at Miami Beach Senior ‚Äã David is leading the effort for the high school club to make prosthetic He is already certified by to make an and a prosthetic The generous grant from Riley‚Äôs Way will pay for additional printers, hand kits from , and additional ‚Äã Helping Hands is also doing weekly Zoom classes on basic electronics and engineering with at Nautilus Middle School in Miami The project is again the only partnership receiving funding from the City of Miami Beach STEAM+ Our Board Jonathan Tamen President David Tamen Vice President of Engineering Lara Gomez Vice President of Business Samantha Pedraza Vice President of Outreach Luis Sprung Build Officer Liam Berko Financial Officer Sofia Smith Marketing Officer ¬©2020 by Helping Proudly created with   Helping Hands | Miami Beach | Home Helping Hands Home About Us Our Projects Contact More Helping Hands Miami Beach, Florida About Helping Hands Helping Hands is a group at Miami Beach Senior High School that uses innovation, technology, and kindness to make a difference in people‚Äôs lives - whether it‚Äôs teaching STEM skills to underrepresented groups in their community or helping to make prosthetic hands for the poor around the Our projects include: Mentoring and language students in coding, robotics, and electronics in elementary and middle school, in partnership with the City of Miami Beach STEAM+ Helping Hands is the only partnership selected by the Teaching printing skills to high school girls and minorities who went on to made hundreds of plastic facial shields for first responders on the frontlines of the Starting a club and an Eagle Scout project to teach students to make prosthetic hands for , an engineering charity that distributes working hand devices to amputees Contact Us ¬©2020 by Helping Proudly created with

Asensys Blockchain: High Performance Blockchain System, Scaled with Asynchronous Consensus Zones in Parallel Asensys ‚Ñ¢ Blockchain Home Technology Technology 2 Research Features Team Investors Contact Twitter Home Technology Technology 2 Research Features Team Investors Contact Unleashing the Limitless Potential of Decentralized The Blockchain System based on Asynchronous Consensus Zones Conquer the Blockchain Trilemma Having a blockchain system is a challenge - some would even say it‚Äôs Various consensus algorithms have been invented to solve the trilemma, but no substantial lift up has been Asensys attacks (and conquers) the trilemma with a unique We have identified that the root cause of the blockchain performance issue is repetition -- every single node is duplicating the workload of the entire network , unless decentralization is Our solution divides and conquers the workload of the entire network with consensus Transactions are processed in parallel and ledgers are maintained in Both throughput and ledger capacity scales linearly with number of zones, with just constant overhead, which makes it possible to have + TPS and carry billions of users and their This goes beyond sharding, without reliance on beacons or root All zones are equal, independent, homogeneous and fully 1 Boundless Scalability Linearly Scaled Throughput and Capacity by Parallel Zones 2 Uncompromised Security Attacking on Any Single Zone is as Hard as on the Entire Network 3 Fully Decentralization No Beacon Chain, or Centralized Coordination Asynchronous Consensus Zones Our key invention is to divide the workload of the entire network into multiple This allows parallel transaction processing and distributed workload of state representation and execution to be realized in a fully decentralized without a beacon or a root Eventual Atomicity This is the key consensus protocol that allows massive parallelism with constant Our programming language PREDA , is delicately and thoughtfully designed for Mining This key protocol ensures security of our system with massive parallel transaction processing when the entire network is divided into multiple Consensus Zones in Parallel [[#ChainAni]] Academy Research Our solution is based on research paper published from the top conference on computer network (NSDI 2019): " Monoxide: Scale out Blockchains with Asynchronous Consensus Zones " Full Paper on USENIX Product Features Blockchain System with High Throughput and State Capacity In Asensys, workloads are distributed across consensus There is no accumulating increasing workload on individual Any node with moderate bandwidth and computation can join the network as a part of the Parallel Relayed Execution Architecture Parallel Distributed Architecture ( PREDA ) adapts functional programming model for defining asynchronous transaction logic and state with Recurrent Transaction Model Asensys supports efficient automatic recurrent transaction, which enables minable token offering, repetitive payment, subscription monetization and flexible staking rewards Programmable Signing Flexible signing and customization transaction validation beyond Our technology is also designed for social private key recovery and enterprise key Random Number Generator with Consensus Asensys offers random number generation in smart contract based on block entropy with consensus, which is resistant to manipulation by block Persistent Storage Asensys enables large data files to be stored for robust persistence without accumulating storage workload on individual Namespace Asensys is shipped with a programmable namespace system, which allows naming for addresses, contracts and Fully Decentralized Applications DApps on Asensys are deployed not only with their smart contract, but also their WebApp asset for This delivers a experience of DApp being fully decentralized without relying on centralized DNS and Web Connect with Us We ll get in touch with you Name TRAIN OF THOUGHT More Posts FROM THE BEGINNING Dx: Q was founded out of a curiosity for how medicine, love, and understanding It was an idea that started in the small, very well decorated, Boston apartment of my friend We were talking about one of several experiences I had where I observed how little the medical community understood the LGBTQ+ We talked about my experience with my primary care physician as well as how teaching staff at my medical school address LGBTQ+ I distinctly remember him being in awe, saying "You should do something about This is not " ‚Äã After we went to bed I realized that this could be happening to more people than I previously I began writing down my thoughts, thinking to myself that indeed something had to be At the top of my notepad in bold was the word I reached out to friends in the queer After a few brave people were willing to share their story with found that the LGBTQ+ community s relationship with healthcare is worse than I From there, over the next few months, Ethan and I created Diagnosis Or as we like to call it, Dx Our experiences in healthcare are intimate, deeply personal, and define our It is Dx: Q s greatest goal to share stories of how the queer community interacts with It is important for more people to understand this relationship and to read the stories of queer individuals who have have benefited by our healthcare system, and have been failed by If you identify with the letters LGBTQ+, you will face challenges when practicing and receiving Queer identity changes the situation for some reason and Dx: Q is here to bring light to this ‚Äã Our hope is that queer visibility will bring Change that can improve the lives of LGBTQ+ ‚Äã Love is Love people, that is always our Thank you for reading and we hope you ‚Äã Peace and Love, ‚Äã Dx:Q FOLLOW DX:Q Contact Us SUBSCRIBE TO DX:Q!
